Seven aspirants have been cleared by the Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission to run for Samburu East MP seat.The candidates including incumbent Raphael Letimalo on the Jubilee Party ticket, Lenas Leshore (ODM), Tom Lalampaa (Narc Kenya), Lekumandare Jackson (Kanu), Mafan Lesanjiri (Chama Cha Mashinani), Benjamin Lemosi (PDU)and Robert Lemarketo (independent)were issued IEBC nomination certificates. They urged voters to elect them on August 8.&ldquo;I plan to address water shortage, food insecurity and improve livelihoods,&rdquo; Lalampaa said. Leshore pledged to lobby for more resources in addition to CDF. He advised youths against misusing social media during the campaign period as it may incite people and create hatred.